physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Hypercalcemia (serum calcium 3.0 mmol/liter, reference values 2.03–2.65 mmol/liter), mild hypophosphatemia (1.13 mmol/liter, normal pediatric reference values 1.5–2.1 mmol/liter), normal intact PTH levels (53 pg/ml, reference values 12–65 pg/ml), and relative hypocalciuria (FeCa 0.0008).
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: At age 11 yr, serum calcium level (3.15 mmol/liter) remained elevated, with PTH of 50 pg/ml (5.3 pmol/liter). Symptoms included vague abdominal pain.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: At 1 month, mildly elevated serum calcium of 2.85 mmol/liter with normal serum PTH level of 33 pg/ml (3.47 pmol/liter).
